==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Coined by Benjamin Franklin, its inventor; built on Italian ''[[armonia]]'', 'harmony'; [[glass harmonica]] is a corruption of Franklin's original word, a [[backformation]] influenced by [[harmonica]] (a reed instrument).

===Noun===

{{en-noun}}
# A musical instrument made of blown-glass bowls mounted on a spindle turned originally by a foot pedal, and played with wetted fingers, producing an ethereal sound. Technically, it is a [[crystallophone]]. It has enjoyed a modern revival.

====Synonyms====
*[[glass harmonica]]

